== Roasted Carrots ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Ginger Rice ==

While carrots roast, peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed), separating whites from greens; mince whites.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the ginger; cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1¼%cups} (2¼ cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Meatballs ==

While rice cooks, in a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, scallion whites, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, remaining ginger, and 1 TBSP @bulgogi sauce{4%ounce} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). (You'll use the rest of the bulgogi sauce in the next step.) Season with @salt{} (we used ¾ tsp; 1 1/2 tsp for 4) and @pepper{}.

Form into 1 1/2-inch meatballs and spread out on a second baking sheet{}.

Bake on middle rack until browned and cooked through, ~{14-16%minutes}.

== Creamy Sriracha ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} with @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste. Add @water{1%tsp} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Once meatballs are done, gently transfer to a second large bowl{}; add remaining bulgogi sauce and toss to coat.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a fork; taste and season with @salt{} if desired.

Divide rice between #plates{} and top with carrots, meatballs, and any bulgogi sauce from bowl. Drizzle with creamy Sriracha. Garnish with scallion greens and as many @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} as you like. Serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.